{{Infobox person | name = Israfil Ashurly | sons = | image = | caption = | birth_date = {{birth date|1969|01|16}} | birth_place = [[Baku]], [[Azerbaijani SSR]], [[USSR]] | nationality = [[Azerbaijani people|Azerbaijani]] | alma_mater = [[Azerbaijan State Oil Academy]] | death_date = | death_place = | occupation = [[Mountaineering|Mountaneer]], [[Explorer]] | networth = | religion = | spouse = Maria Ashurly | residence = Baku, Azerbaijan | children = Aslan Ashurly and Ali Ashurly | awards = [[Tereggi Medal]] | website = | signature = }}
'''Israfil Ashurly''' ({{lang-az|İsrafil Aşurlu}}; born January 16, 1969 in [[Baku]], [[Azerbaijani SSR]], [[USSR]]) is a [[mountaineer]], [[explorer]], general secretary of Ice-Climbing Commission and Competition, owner of Insol company and president of Azerbaijan Mountaneering Federation.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Rasulova|first1=Farida|script-title=ru:Президент Федерации альпинизма Азербайджана Исрафил Ашурлы рассказал о достижениях и планах азербайджанских альпинистов|url=http://1news.az/sport/others/20131223032739802.html|website=1news.az|accessdate=17 August 2014|language=Russian}}</ref> He was the first Azerbaijani to climb [[Mount Everest]] and [[Kangchenjunga]], completing the [[Seven Summits]] challenge in 2007.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Hamill|first1=Mike|title=Climbing the Seven Summits: A Comprehensive Guide to the Continents' Highest Peaks|date=2012|publisher=The Mountaineers Books|page=293}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|script-title=ru:Список покорителей 7 вершин (по состоянию на начало 2009 года)|url=http://7summits.ru/articles/all/item_1859/|website=7summits.ru|accessdate=17 August 2014|language=Russian}}</ref> He is also first Azerbaijani to receive [[Snow Leopard award]]<ref>{{cite web|title=History of alpinism in Azerbaijan|url=http://aaf.az/eng/info/history/|website=aaf.az|accessdate=17 August 2014}}</ref> and [[Volcanic Seven Summits]] in 2009 and first undisputed Azerbaijani explorer to walk on the [[North Pole]] in 2009.<ref name=trend>{{cite web|title=Исрафил Ашурлы отмечен в Москве почетным знаком "Покоритель Эвереста" (фото)|url=http://www.trend.az/life/interesting/2087301.html|website=www.trend.az|accessdate=17 August 2014}}</ref>
==Biography== He graduated from [[Azerbaijan State Oil Academy]]'s energy faculty.<ref name=1newz/> In 1991, Ashurly set-up "Insol", a company engaged since 1998, installation and commissioning of telecommunication equipment for mobile and wired communications in Russia.<ref name=1newz>{{cite web|last1=Aleksandarova|first1=Natalie|script-title=ru:ФОРМУЛА УСПЕХА. Исрафил Ашурлы: «Тогда я и не знал, что получу уникальный шанс взойти на Эверест и поднять там флаг Азербайджана…»|url=http://www.1news.az/interview/formulau/20130125123424221.html|website=www.1news.az|accessdate=17 August 2014|language=Russian}}</ref>
He was awarded "Edelweiss" order for completing The Seven Summits in 2008.<ref>{{cite web|title=Alpinist mükafatlandırıldı|url=http://hafta.az/index2.php?m=yazi&id=62031|website=hafta.az|accessdate=17 August 2014|language=Azerbaijani}}</ref> In 2009, he received [[Tereggi Medal]] for his contributions to development of mountaneering in Azerbaijan.<ref name=trend/> On 22 October 2014, his cousin [[Murad Ashurly]], also mountaineer and third Azerbaijani to reach Everest, has died on a return journey after successfully ascending the Mount [[Ama Dablam]] in the [[Himalaya]] range.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Akhundov|first1=Murad|script-title=ru:Азербайджанский альпинист Мурад Ашурлы пропал безвести в Гималаях – ФОТО|url=http://www.1news.az/sport/others/20141023010548588.html|website=www.1news.az|accessdate=22 October 2014|language=Russian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=В ГИМАЛАЯХ ПОГИБ БРАТ ПРЕЗИДЕНТА АЗЕРБАЙДЖАНСКОЙ ФЕДЕРАЦИИ|url=http://vesti.az/news/222778|website=vesti.az|accessdate=22 October 2014}}</ref>
==Expeditions== In 2000, while on a holiday visit to near [[Kangchenjunga]]'s foot, Ashurly became interested in [[mountaineering]]. In next seven years, he became ninth person to complete [[Seven Summits]] challenge.<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ru:ПЕРВЫЙ АЗЕРБАЙДЖАНСКИЙ АЛЬПИНИСТ, ПОКОРИВШИЙ ЭВЕРЕСТ - ИСРАФИЛ АШУРЛУ ОТПРАВЛЯЕТСЯ ТЕПЕРЬ НА ПОКОРЕНИЕ СЕВЕРНОГО ПОЛЮСА|url=http://www.mediaforum.az/rus/2009/03/16/%D0%9F%D0%95%D0%A0%D0%92%D0%AB%D0%99-%D0%90%D0%97%D0%95%D0%A0%D0%91%D0%90%D0%99%D0%94%D0%96%D0%90%D0%9D%D0%A1%D0%9A%D0%98%D0%99-%D0%90%D0%9B%D0%AC%D0%9F%D0%98%D0%9D%D0%98%D0%A1%D0%A2-%D0%9F%D0%9E%D0%9A%D0%9E%D0%A0%D0%98%D0%92%D0%A8%D0%98%D0%99-%D0%AD%D0%92%D0%95%D0%A0%D0%95%D0%A1%D0%A2-035455575c10.html#.U_C9L_ldVQA|website=www.mediaforum.az|accessdate=17 August 2014|language=Russian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Interview with Israfil Ashurly|url=http://www.russianclimb.com/elbrus_israfil_interview.html|website=www.russianclimb.com|accessdate=17 August 2014}}</ref>
