===Himalayas expeditions=== In 2003, he reached [[Lapchi mountain]] (6,017) with Russian [[alpinist]] [[Vladimir Shatayev]].<ref>{{cite web|title=One unconquered mountain in Nepal has decreased.|url=http://lacota.net/adventure-tourism-and-recreation/one-unconquered-mountain-in-nepal-has-been-lower-.html|website=lacota.net|accessdate=17 August 2014}}</ref> In 2007, Ashurly reached [[Everest]] with [[Sergey Kofanov]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Everest 2007: Sergey Kofanov report and video concerning rescue of Marco Epis|url=http://www.everestnews.com/everest2007/everest06042007.htm|website=www.everestnews.com|accessdate=17 August 2014}}</ref> In 2011, he reached [[Kangchenjunga]] with Russian alpinists [[Aleksey Bolotov]] and [[Nikolay Totmyanin]].<ref>{{cite web|title=7 Summits Everest Expedition Tibet 2011: Base Camp|url=http://www.everestnews.com/stories2011/7summitstibet04252011.htm|website=www.everestnews.com|accessdate=17 August 2014}}</ref>
