{{Use British English|date=December 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=December 2014}} {{Hatnote|For his grandchild, '''José Armando Bermúdez (1928–2014)''', and the 3rd CEO of J. A. Bermúdez, see '''[[José Armando Bermúdez Pippa]]'''. For the '''national park''', see '''[[José Armando Bermúdez National Park]]'''.}}
'''José Armando Bermúdez Rochet'''{{#tag:ref|{{Spanish name|'''Bermúdez'''|'''Rochet'''|plain=yes}}|group="nb"|name=""}} (1871–1941) was a [[People of the Dominican Republic|Dominican]] businessman and the founder of '''[[Bermúdez (rum)|J. Armando Bermúdez & Co., C. por A.]]'''. The [[José Armando Bermúdez National Park|José Armando Bermúdez]] [[National Park]] is named in his honour.
He was born on 28 April 1871 to Erasmo Bermúdez Jiménez (1825-1907), a [[Venezuelan people|Venezuelan]] immigrant, and Petronila Rochet Gómez (1839–1889), the daughter of a [[French people|French]] immigrant of Belgian Walloon and French descent.<ref name=Espinal>{{cite news|last1=Espinal|first1=Edwin|title=Los apellidos del ron: Bermúdez|url=http://hoy.com.do/capsulas-genealogicaslos-apellidos-del-ron-bermudez/|accessdate=4 December 2014|work=Cápsulas Genealógicas|agency=Instituto Dominicano de Genealogía|publisher=Hoy|date=29 August 2009|language=Spanish}}</ref>
In 1899 he married Ana Luisa Ramos de Peña and begat 6 children, all males: José Ignacio (1899-1968), Aquiles (1901-1970), [[Domingo Octavio Bermúdez|Domingo Octavio]] (1902-1967), Luis Francisco ‘Frank’ (1904-1949), Víctor Manuel ‘Tontón’ (1906-1959) and Fernando Arturo (1909-1955).<ref name=Espinal/>
Bermúdez died on 4 October 1941.<ref name=Espinal/>
