{{BLP unsourced|date=January 2016}} {{Infobox person | name = Nigar Kocharli | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = Nigar Köçərli | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1975|10|15}} | birth_place = [[Baku]], [[Azerbaijan]] | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = [[Azerbaijan]]i | other_names = | known_for = | occupation = Publisher and Bookseller }}
'''Nigar Kocharli''' (born 15 October 1975) is the [[Chief Executive Officer|CEO]] and owner of the Ali and Nino [[bookstore]] [[chain store|chain]] and publishing house, and founder of the National Book Award of Azerbaijan.
Kocharli graduated from [[Baku State University]] and was part of the [[mathematics]] faculty between 1993 and 1997.
Kocharli worked for several companies and projects after graduation, including the [[United Nations Development Programme]] Community Empowerment Project up until 2001. In that year she started a business, establishing Ali and Nino, which is the now the largest [[bookstore]] [[chain store|chain]] in Azerbaijan. The chain is named after the novel ''[[Ali and Nino]]''. Soon after opening the bookstores, she founded the National Book Award, aiming to promote modern [[Azerbaijani literature]] and support local authors.
Kocharli also established an online bookstore selling books in [[Azerbaijani language|Azerbaijani]], [[Turkish language|Turkish]], [[Russian language|Russian]] and [[English language|English]], as well as founding Ali and Nino Publishing House, which translates and publishes [[classics]] and contemporary literature, including the novels of [[Khalid Hosseini]].
Kocharli is married and has one daughter.
