'''Vanich Chaiyawan''' (born 1931) is a Thai [[billionaire]] businessman, chairman of [[Thai Life Insurance]], the second-largest life insurer in Thailand.
==Early life== Vanich Chaiyawan was born in 1931.<ref name=Forbes/> He comes from a [[Thai Chinese]] family.<ref name="google">{{cite book|title=The Oxford Handbook of Business Groups|author1=Colpan, A.M.|author2=Hikino, T.|author3=Lincoln, J.R.|date=2010|publisher=OUP Oxford|isbn=9780199552863|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RL2pWCa9Z24C&pg=PA250|page=250|accessdate=30 July 2017}}</ref>
==Career== Chaiyawan owns about 60% of Thai Life, which is now run by his son [[Chai Chaiyawan]] as president.<ref name=Forbes/> He also owns Thai Asia Pacific Brewery and Thai Credit Retail Bank.{{citation needed|date=December 2017}}
==Personal life== He is married with eight children and lives in [[Bangkok]].<ref name=Forbes/>
